{"first_name":"Steve","last_name":"O'Hear","permalink":"steve-ohear","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/steve-ohear","homepage_url":"http://www.ohear.net","birthplace":"London","twitter_username":"sohear","blog_url":"http://www.last100.com","blog_feed_url":"http://feeds2.feedburner.com/last100","affiliation_name":"ReadWriteWeb","born_year":1975,"born_month":6,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Mon Nov 16 13:48:30 UTC 2009","updated_at":"Thu Dec 06 18:50:26 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Steve O&#8217;Hear is probably best known as a technology journalist, currently at TechCrunch where he focuses mainly on European/UK startups, companies and products.</p>\n\n<p>From April 2011 to February 2012, he was co-founder and CEO of expertise platform Beepl where he helped the company navigate its first VC round, along with seeing the product through development, private alpha and a high profile public launch. Beepl was acquired by Brand Embassy in November 2012.</p>\n\n<p>Along with TechCrunch and last100, Steve has written for numerous publications, including The Guardian, Macworld UK, Mobile Industry Review, TES, ZDNet and ReadWriteWeb, on topics ranging from the social web, educational technology to consumer electronics. From 2006 to 2008 he wrote the ZDNet blog &#8216;The Social Web&#8217;. Steve also wrote and directed the critically acclaimed Silicon Valley documentary &#8216;In Search of the Valley&#8217;, which was released in September 2006.</p>\n\n<p>In 2002 Steve was made a fellow of the National Endowment for Science, Technology and the Arts. Fom 2004 to 2005 he served on the board of governors for the University of East London.</p>\n\n<p>Steve is also one half of ProtoBake Labs, an &#8216;ideas incubator&#8217; he co-founded with Pete Harris.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[149,150],"assets/images/resized/0006/6412/66412v10-max-150x150.png"],[[249,250],"assets/images/resized/0006/6412/66412v10-max-250x250.png"],[[449,450],"